
[1]approbation

   APPROBA'TION, n. [L. approbatio. See Proof and Prove.]

   1. The act of approving; a liking; that state or disposition of the
   mind, in which we assent to the propriety of a thing, with some degree
   of pleasure or satisfaction; as, the laws of God require our
   approbation.

   2. Attestation; support; that is, active approbation, or action in
   favor of what is approved.

   3. The commendation of a book licensed or permitted to be published by
   authority, as was formerly the case in England.
